738
00:38:44.192 --> 00:38:45.626
ALEX: What? What is it?

739
00:38:46.227 --> 00:38:48.229
DANIEL: You see that gap
between the trees?

740
00:38:48.830 --> 00:38:50.965
There are
no straight lines in nature.

741
00:38:51.933 --> 00:38:52.967
No. there are not.

742
00:38:57.404 --> 00:39:02.442
(ANIMALS CHITTERING)
(BIRDS CALLING)

743
00:39:14.589 --> 00:39:16.824
Railroad tracks
always lead somewhere.

744
00:39:19.227 --> 00:39:21.262
ALEX: Which direction?
This way.

745
00:39:21.629 --> 00:39:25.533
How do you know?
I don't. Just being decisive.

746
00:39:32.439 --> 00:39:35.543
(DISTANT OWL HOOTING)

747
00:39:42.884 --> 00:39:43.951
